{
  "text": "Note that the second technical condition is not necessary, but simplifies things. It is also partially justified by [CITATION_1] . Indeed, realize that T has the interpretation of the class of sets S such that it might be the case that c G (S ) = 1 for an optimal graph G. Provided c G (S ) = 1, the condition (1) implies that c G (T ) = 1 for quite many subsets T of S with |T | ≥ 2. Therefore, if S ∈ T , it makes sense to allow T ∈ T for any T ⊆ S , |T | ≥ 2.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "6552932"
  },
  "bib_entries": {
    "6552932": {
      "title": "Branching rules revisited",
      "abstract": "We present a new generalization called reliability branching of today's state-of-the-art strong branching and pseudocost branching strategies for linear programming based branch-and-bound algorithms. After reviewing commonly used branching strategies and performing extensive computational studies we compare different parameter settings and show the superiority of our proposed new strategy."
    }
  }
}